# Local privacy pattern list for the T-CLEAN linter (must never be committed)
personal-patterns.txt

# Per-machine tool settings. These MUST be named here rather than left to an operator's personal
# global gitignore: the release rebuild deliberately ignores the global file so that what ships
# depends on this repository alone, which means a path only the global file excludes is a path this
# repo would happily publish. .claude/settings.local.json records approved tool permissions and local
# paths, and it appears the first time a permission is approved for this project.
.claude/settings.local.json
*.local.json

# Editor and OS residue. Named here for the same reason: the release preflight reads the tree with
# THIS file's rules only, ignoring the operator's personal global gitignore, so anything the repo does
# not classify stops a release. `*.orig` and `*.rej` appear after every conflicted merge or rebase,
# and the resulting abort names files the operator's own `git status` insists do not exist.
*~
*.swp
*.orig
*.rej
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Local database(s) at the project root
between.db*

# "Your data" -> Back up now writes timestamped copies here (they are databases; never commit one)
/backups/
examples/backups/

# Secrets / environment
.env
.env.*
*.key
*.pem

