# Private exploration handoff (personal findings — never commit)
docs/FABLE-EXPLORATION.md

# Author's private development journal — reads as a personal log of user zero's own archive
# (aggregate stats, decisions). Kept out of the public repo; the design brief (between-brief.html)
# and the test plan (TESTING.md) stay in, name-detached.
docs/DECISIONS.md

# The internal build scaffolding. These were published from v0.1.0 through v0.3.2 and should never
# have been: they are the contract between a planning phase and a build phase, written for whoever was
# building, and they carry two kinds of thing the public repo must not.
#
# The first is PERSONAL DATA about the author's own archive — its exact size and message counts, its
# span, the number of people in it, and the literal local path it sits at. HANDOFF.md states, as
# binding invariant 3, "No personal data in code, prompts, tests, or the repo — ever". It then gives
# the counts. The document announcing the rule was the clearest breach of it.
#
# The second is the private shape of how this was made: which model did which job, phase gates,
# division of labour. Not dangerous, just nobody else's business and not a description of the product.
#
# They stay on phase3 because they are a real record of how this was built. They are simply not
# publishable, and the release rebuild drops them the same way it drops the journal.
HANDOFF.md
GAMEPLAN.md
docs/GAMEPLAN-PHASE3.md
docs/HANDOFF-READINESS.md

# Built demo bundle (produced by `npm run demo:build`, assembled in CI for Pages).
# The captured DATA in site/demo-data IS tracked and reviewable; the bundle is not.
site/demo/
